## Netlify Edge Functions vs Supabase Edge Functions

| | Netlify Edge Functions | Supabase Edge Functions |
|---|---|---|
| Runtime | Deno (Netlify's own) | Deno (Supabase's runtime) |
| Latency | Runs closest to user | Runs closest to user |
| Database access | Via Supabase REST API | Via direct Supabase client |
| Auth | Manual JWT verification | Built-in JWT validation |
| Cold starts | Yes | Yes |
| Max duration | 30s | 150s (400s background) |
| Secrets | Netlify env vars | Supabase secrets |
| Deploy | Part of Next.js build | Separate deploy step |
| Best for | Auth middleware, geo-routing, A/B | DB operations, AI, webhooks |

**Rule:** Use Netlify middleware for routing/auth checks. Use Supabase Edge Functions for anything that touches the DB or requires long computation.

